args: Are you sure this is a good idea, Ranzal?
Sneaking around after one of our comrades\njust feels...wrong.
Aw, it's fine. Ain't like we're followin' him\naround to jump him or blackmail him or\nsomethin', yeah?
Still, lurking around in silence behind him\ndoesn't really sit well with me.
Yeah, but if we don't do this, we'll never\nfigure out what Edward's flaws are!
Knowin' yer friends' weaknesses can\nhelp ya protect 'em better, right?
Right?! So let's make with the tailin'\nalready!
Let's see, the construction of the candy\nhouse is currently at about 70 percent\ncompletion, so... Ah, Madam Cleo?
I've finished ordering the additional flour\nand sugar needed to complete the\nSweet Retreat.
The goods are scheduled for delivery\ntomorrow, so if you'd be so kind as to\nreceive them, I would be grateful.
Well, that's a help. We were just about\nto run out of those things.
All of this is to ensure the smooth and\nprompt progress of our Halloween\npreparations.
Cleo? Edward? I'm going on patrol.
As I've already completed the north and \neast patrols, I'd be most grateful if you\ncould take care of the others.
Such is expected of a butler like myself.
...That sounds like Edward, all right.\nHe always performs his duties admirably.
Yeah, but what's he still doin' dressed\nin that crazy getup?
Apparently it's so he's prepared in case\nfiends attack at some point.
Yeah, or maybe he actually just likes it.
I bet it awakened some primal urge what\nto run around in a costume and—
Incorrect. This is no matter of play.
H-how did you know we were here...?
How could I not, with the very obvious\nway in which you two went about trying\nto shadow me?
First of all, you weren't able to hide\nyour tracks.
Furthermore, you may have been trying\nto whisper, but your voices are echoing\nover hill and dale.
Honestly, are your hearts even in this\nlittle endeavor of yours?
And whyever are you fumbling about the\nplace in an attempt to keep tabs on me?
Well, uhh...we were just thinkin' it's gotta\nbe hard to work when you're runnin' around\nin that unusual outfit, yeah?
We were worried about ya! Ain't that right,\n{player_name}?!
Muh?! You didn't say one word abou—
Shhhh! We were supposed to have our\nstories straight!

*sigh* Master Ranzal, would you be kind
enough to desist in trying to indoctrinate
Master {player_name} into your
wily—and rather inane—ways?
I wonder, perhaps, if you weren't tempting\nhim into making an attempt at identifying\nany potential flaws of mine?
Uhhhh, nope! Not at all! That wasn't what\nwe were up to at all! Nooooo, sir.
You truly are as simple to read as a bit of\nchildren's verse. You think it hard to work\nin this ＂unusual outfit＂?
Very well. I will prove to the two of you\njust how unnecessary such concerns are.
...Okay, so now we're in the kitchen.\nAre you seriously about to start cooking\nsomething?
I am. Let us prepare samples of the food\nfor the Halloween celebration.\n
Er, with you dressed like that?
That collar and coat look like they'd really\nget in the way.
Amazing! He's cutting those vegetables\ninto spiderweb shapes!
Ah, but I'm not through yet!
Now he's hollowing out that pumpkin like\nit's nothing!
And that ain't all—he's carvin' a design\nin the pumpkin AND makin' a buncha\nother grub!
A spiderweb-themed salad, and a stew\nhoused in a pumpkin vessel.
Well, all right... *chomp* Oh my gosh,\nEdward.
The taste is great, and it looks even MORE\nincredible!
I'm deeply grateful for your kind words.\nNow, does this help you to understand?
My work and my dress have no bearing on\none another.
If necessary, I would execute my master's\nwishes to perfection even while clad in\nnothing at all.
Um, you can keep your clothes on.
Still, you really are perfect, Edward.
Maybe he doesn't have any flaws\nafter all...
